Bump!
What about a new configurable setting like set::history::channel::playback-on-join::disable-on-bots
Example:
set {
        history {
                channel {
                        /* How many lines to playback on join? */
                        playback-on-join {
                                disable-on-bots yes; // <--------------------
                                lines 15;
                                time 1d;
                        }
                        /* How much history to keep. These are the
                         * upper maximums for channel mode +H lines:time
                         */
                        max-storage-per-channel {
                                lines 200;
                                time 1w;
                        }
                }
        }
}

column20:
The goal of this patch is allowing the following syntax for deny link blocks:
deny link {
	mask {
		*;
		!foobar.hub;
	};
	rule !connected(foobar.hub);
	type all;
};

to prevent the current server from accepting connections from other leaf servers while the server is separated to the network (to prevent leaves with multiple autoconnects from bridging between two hubs)

